From CASPER PPE Subject Re American Jewish Congress Open Letter to Clinton In article Ken Arromdee In article CASPER PPE writes Are you aware that there is an arms embargo on all of what is was Yugoslavia including Bosnia which guarantees massive military superiority of Serbian forces and does not allow the Bosnians to try to defend themselves Should we sell weapons to all sides or just the losing one then Ending an embargo does not we must sell anything at We'll probably end up giving them If the Europeans want to sell weapons to one or both sides they are welcome as far as I'm You seem to oppose ending the You know it is difficult for Europeans to sell weapons when there is an embargo in During WWII the British managed to supply arms to the Yugoslavs despite German If the Europeans had the will to do anything besides sponsoring peace conferences they would have no problem putting any kind of weapon they wanted into I guess I would favor ending the embargo if the Congress would pass a law forbidding export of US military supplies to Yugoslavia including via third Until then the risks of the US being drawn into a more active role would be too I do not see the arms embargo as a major factor in the outcome of the I do not automatically accept the argument that Bosnia is any worse than other recent civil wars say Vietnam for The difference is it is happening to white people inside Europe with lots of TV But if this was the reason and if furthermore both sides are equal wouldn't all us racist Americans be favoring the good Christians Serbs instead of the non Christians we really seem to favor Both sides are certainly not equal in the eyes of the And that's about all we have to go on isn't it And I wish you'd quit hurling words like racist There are many levels at which people react to what they At the most fundamental level you do not have to consciously recognize the racial element you simply tend to empathize more with people who are like As far preferring Christian over Moslem I am an atheist myself and I think you'll agree that in the US the majority of people do not typically discriminate on the basis of religion nor give it a particularly important place in their world Dave